This paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category as it focuses on improving the performance of data center networks through a new TCP congestion control algorithm. It may also fall under the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category as it addresses the issue of buffer overflow and packet loss, which can be exploited by attackers. The paper also involves system-level design and implementation, which could place it in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category. Additionally, it deals with information theory and communication, which could make it relevant to the Information Theory (cs.IT) category. Finally, the paper involves performance evaluation and optimization, which could place it in the Performance (cs.PF) category.
